\[\sqrt{s(s - x)(s - x)(s - 30)} = r \cdot (s - x),\]where $s = x + 15.$  Hence,
\[\sqrt{(x + 15)(x - 15)^2 \cdot 15} = r \cdot 15.\]Then
\[(x + 15)(x - 15) = 15r^2.\]Since $CI$ is an angle bisector, $\triangle BCI$ is isosceles, so $BI = CI = \frac{x}{2}.$  Then by the Pythagorean theorem on right triangle $BCI,$
\[BI^2 = CI^2 - BC^2 = x^2 - 900.\]Hence,
\[r = \frac{(x + 15)(x - 15)}{15x} = \frac{x^2 - 225}{15x} = \frac{x^2 - 900 - 675}{15x} = \frac{BI^2 - 675}{15 \cdot BI}.\]Since $BI = \frac{x}{2},$
\[r = \frac{\left( \frac{x}{2} \right)^2 - 675}{15 \cdot \frac{x}{2}} = \frac{x^2 - 2700}{60x} = \frac{x^2 - 900 - 1800}{60x} = \frac{BI^2 - IC^2}{60 \cdot BI}.\]Then by the Pythagorean theorem on right triangle $BCI,$
\[r = \frac{BI^2 - IC^2}{60 \cdot BI} = \frac{x^2 - (18^2 - x^2)}{60 \cdot BI} = \frac{2x^2 - 18^2}{60 \cdot BI}.\]Hence,
